315 else if (strncmp(first_chars, "%=SNX", 5) == 0)
316 {
317 // Set the file type
318 input_file_meta->filetype = sinex;
319 m_ift = sinex;
320 m_idt = stn_msr_data;
321
322 // Parse the SINEX file and capture the epoch
323 ParseSNX(fileName, vStations, stnCount, vMeasurements, msrCount, clusterID);
324
325 // Since SINEX files do not permit recording of reference frame within the file, set
326 // the frame to the default reference frame
327 snprintf(input_file_meta->epsgCode, sizeof(input_file_meta->epsgCode), "%s", m_strProjectDefaultEpsg.substr(0, STN_EPSG_WIDTH).c_str());
328 snprintf(input_file_meta->epoch, sizeof(input_file_meta->epoch), "%s", datum_.GetEpoch_s().substr(0, STN_EPOCH_WIDTH).c_str());
329
330 if (firstFile)
331 {
332 fileEpoch = input_file_meta->epoch;
333 if (!fileEpoch.empty())
334 m_strProjectDefaultEpoch = fileEpoch;
335 }
336
337 SignalComplete();
338 }
339 // STN or MSR
340 else if (
341 // use boost::algorithm::ifind_first, which is a case insensitive implementation of the find first algorithm.
342 strncmp(first_chars, "!#=DNA", 6) == 0 || // dna file?
343 boost::ifind_first(fileName, ".stn") || // dna station file
344 boost::ifind_first(fileName, ".msr")) // dna measurement file
345 {
346 // Set the file type
347 input_file_meta->filetype = dna;
348 m_ift = dna;
349
350 // Parse the DNA file
351 ParseDNA(fileName, vStations, stnCount, vMeasurements, msrCount, clusterID, fileEpsg, fileEpoch, firstFile);
352
353 if (fileEpsg.empty())
354 fileEpsg = m_strProjectDefaultEpsg;
355
356 // record the file's default reference frame
357 snprintf(input_file_meta->epsgCode, sizeof(input_file_meta->epsgCode), "%s", fileEpsg.substr(0, STN_EPSG_WIDTH).c_str());
358 snprintf(input_file_meta->epoch, sizeof(input_file_meta->epoch), "%s", fileEpoch.substr(0, STN_EPOCH_WIDTH).c_str());
359
360 SignalComplete();
361 }
362 else
363 {
364 //throw XMLInteropException("ParseInputFile(): Could not deduce file type from extension or contents.", 0);
365 ss.str("");
366 ss << "ParseInputFile(): " << leafStr<std::string>(fileName) << " is not a recognised station or" << std::endl <<
367 " measurement input file.";
368 (*success_msg) = ss.str();
369 //SignalExceptionParse(ss.str(), 0);
370 parseStatus_ = PARSE_UNRECOGNISED_FILE;
371 throw XMLInteropException(ss.str(), 0);
372 }
374
375 // Apply discontinuities (if they exist) to each file except SINEX
376 // SINEX files are automatically handled
377 if (m_ift != sinex)
378 {
379 if (p->i.apply_discontinuities)
380 ApplyDiscontinuities(vMeasurements);
381 }
382
383 // Populate metadata
384 snprintf(input_file_meta->filename, sizeof(input_file_meta->filename), "%s", fileName.c_str());
385 if (*stnCount > 0 && *msrCount > 0)
386 input_file_meta->datatype = stn_msr_data;
387 else if (*stnCount > 0)
388 input_file_meta->datatype = stn_data;
389 else if (*msrCount > 0)
390 input_file_meta->datatype = msr_data;
391
392 return parseStatus_;
393}

5263 _it_vdnamsrptr _it_msrG(vMeasurementsG.begin());
5264 vstring stationsX;
5265 std::vector<CDnaGpsBaseline> *vgpsBslsX, *vgpsBslsG;
5266 std::string epochX, epochG;
5267 boost::gregorian::date dateObsX, dateObsG;
5268 std::stringstream strdiffDays;
5269 size_t diffDays;
5270 vUINT32 cluster_ids;
5271
5272 // For each X Cluster, get the list of stations
5273 for (_it_vdnamsrptr _it_msrX(vMeasurementsX.begin()); _it_msrX!=vMeasurementsX.end(); ++_it_msrX)
5274 {
5275 vgpsBslsX = _it_msrX->get()->GetBaselines_ptr();
5276 GetGXMsrStations<std::string>(vgpsBslsX, stationsX);
5277
5278 std::sort(stationsX.begin(), stationsX.end());
5279
5280 similarG = false;
5281
5282 // Check whether both stations in the G baseline exist
5283 // in the list of X Cluster stations
5284 for (_it_msrG=vMeasurementsG.begin(); _it_msrG!=vMeasurementsG.end(); ++_it_msrG)
5285 {
5286 vgpsBslsG = _it_msrG->get()->GetBaselines_ptr();
5287
5288 // Is the first G baseline station in the cluster?
5289 if (!binary_search(stationsX.begin(), stationsX.end(), vgpsBslsG->at(0).GetFirst()))
5290 // No, then this isn't a "duplicate"
5291 continue;
5292
5293 // Is the second G baseline station in the cluster?
5294 if (!binary_search(stationsX.begin(), stationsX.end(), vgpsBslsG->at(0).GetTarget()))
5295 // No, then this isn't a "duplicate"
5296 continue;
5297
5298 // Okay, both stations are in the cluster... check if this is a "duplicate"
5299 // by examining epoch. Here, the assumption is - if the observation epochs of the
5300 // X and G measurements are the same, then the X and G measurements have come from
5301 // the same source data and are therefore duplicates
5302 epochX = _it_msrX->get()->GetEpoch();
5303 epochG = _it_msrG->get()->GetEpoch();
5304
5305 dateObsX = dateFromString<boost::gregorian::date>(epochX);
5306 dateObsG = dateFromString<boost::gregorian::date>(epochG);
5307
5308 boost::gregorian::days dateDifference = dateObsX - dateObsG;
5309
5310 diffDays = abs(dateDifference.days());
5311 //strdiffDays << "Elapsed days: " << dateDifference;
5312 //TRACE("%s\n", strdiffDays.str().c_str());
5313
5314 if (diffDays < 5)
5315 {
5316 ++similar_msrs_found;
5317 similarG = true;
5318 vSimilarMeasurements->push_back(*_it_msrG);
5319 if (projectSettings_.i.ignore_similar_msr)
5320 cluster_ids.push_back(_it_msrG->get()->GetClusterID());
5321 }
5322 }
5323
5324 // Were similar G baselines found for this cluster?
5325 if (similarG)
5326 vSimilarMeasurements->push_back(*_it_msrX);
5327
5328 }
5329
5330 // If required, ignore the measurements
5331 if (projectSettings_.i.ignore_similar_msr)
5332 {
5333 std::sort(cluster_ids.begin(), cluster_ids.end());
5334 for (_it_msrG=vMeasurements->begin(); _it_msrG != vMeasurements->end(); _it_msrG++)
5335 IgnoreGXMeasurements(_it_msrG->get(), cluster_ids.begin(), cluster_ids.end());
5336 }
5337
5338 return similar_msrs_found;
5339}

574 SignalExceptionParse(static_cast<std::string>(ss.str()), 0);
575 }
576 catch (const std::system_error& e)
577 {
578 if (ifsInputFILE_->eof())
579 {

581 import_file_mutex.unlock();

585 {

593 }
594 catch (const XMLInteropException& e)
595 {
596 std::stringstream ss;

600 catch (const ::xml_schema::parsing& e)
601 {

607 {

609 ss << " - line " << _it->line();
610 ss << ", column " << _it->column();
611 ss << ", severity " << _it->severity() << std::endl;
612 ss << " - " << _it->message();

615 }
616 catch (const ::xml_schema::exception& e)

622 catch (...)

626 SignalExceptionParse(ss.str(), 0);

630 {

2814
2815 // Target station
2816 if (msr_ptr->GetMsrStnCount() >= TWO_STATION)
2817 msr_ptr->SetTarget(ParseTargetValue(sBuf, "ParseDNAMSRDirections"));
2818
2819 // Number of directions
2820 UINT32 dirnCount, dirnCountLessIgnored;
2821 msr_ptr->SetTotal(ParseMsrCountValue(sBuf, dirnCount, "ParseDNAMSRDirections"));
2822 msr_ptr->GetDirections_ptr()->reserve(dirnCount);
2823
2824 CDnaDirection dirnTmp;
2825 dirnTmp.SetRecordedTotal(0);
2826
2827 // If import is being used to simulate measurements, return as the
2828 // expected input is:
2829 // Measurement
2830 // From station
2831 // To station
2832 // So no need to read direction values or database ID
2833 if (!projectSettings_.i.simulate_measurements)
2834 {
2835 // Value
2836 msr_ptr->SetValue(ParseAngularValue(sBuf, "ParseDNAMSRDirections"));
2837
2838 // Standard deviation
2839 msr_ptr->SetStdDev(ParseStdDevValue(sBuf, "ParseDNAMSRDirections"));
2840
2841 // Epoch
2842 msr_ptr->SetEpoch(ParseEpochValue(sBuf, "ParseDNAMSRDirections"));
2843
2844 // Capture msr_id and cluster_id (for database referencing)
2845 ParseDatabaseIds(sBuf, "ParseDNAMSRDirections", msr_ptr->GetTypeC());
2846 msr_ptr->SetDatabaseMap(m_msr_db_map);
2847 dirnTmp.SetClusterID(msr_ptr->GetClusterID());
2848 }
2849
2850 bool subignoreMsr;
2851 dirnCountLessIgnored = dirnCount;
2852
2853 if (dirnCount == 0)
2854 throw XMLInteropException("Zero direction count.", m_lineNo);
2855
2856 for (UINT32 dirn=0; dirn<dirnCount; ++dirn)
2857 {
2858 m_lineNo++;
2859 // Obtain exclusive use of the input file pointer
2860 import_file_mutex.lock();
2861 getline((*ifsInputFILE_), sBuf);
2862 // release file pointer mutex
2863 import_file_mutex.unlock();
2864
2865 // get ignore flag for sub direction and remove accordingly
2866 subignoreMsr = boost::iequals("*", sBuf.substr(dml_.msr_ignore, dmw_.msr_ignore));
2867
2868 if (subignoreMsr)
2869 {
2870 dirnCountLessIgnored--;
2871 if (dirnCountLessIgnored == 0)
2872 {
2873 // throw if the entire direction set is not ignored
2874 if (!ignoreMsr)
2875 throw XMLInteropException("There aren't any non-ignored directions in the set.", m_lineNo);
2876 }
2877 }
2878
2879 dirnTmp.SetFirst(msr_ptr->GetFirst());
2880 dirnTmp.SetIgnore(subignoreMsr);
2881 g_parsemsr_tally.D++;
2882
2883 // Second target station
2884 dirnTmp.SetTarget(ParseTarget2Value(sBuf, "ParseDNAMSRDirections"));
2885
2886 // Again, no need to read direction values
2887 if (!projectSettings_.i.simulate_measurements)
2888 {
2889 // Value
2890 dirnTmp.SetValue(ParseAngularValue(sBuf, "ParseDNAMSRDirections"));
2891
2892 // Standard deviation
2893 dirnTmp.SetStdDev(ParseStdDevValue(sBuf, "ParseDNAMSRDirections"));

2896 ParseDatabaseIds(sBuf, "ParseDNAMSRDirections", msr_ptr->GetTypeC());
2897 dirnTmp.SetDatabaseMap(m_msr_db_map);
2898 }
2899
2900 // add the direction
2901 msr_ptr->AddDirection(((CDnaMeasurement*)&dirnTmp));
2902 }
2903
2904 msr_ptr->SetNonIgnoredDirns(dirnCountLessIgnored);
2905
2906 return dirnCount;

3312 erase_if(vgpsBsls, CompareIgnoreedClusterMeas<CDnaGpsBaseline>());
